The paper deals with generating descriptive captions for images, which is a well-researched area in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel metric for evaluating the generated captions, which focuses on the subject, predicate, object, and product name, indicating a natural language processing (NLP) component (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural network architecture and multi-task learning, indicating a machine learning (ML) component (cs.MM, cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing the caption quality, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI).
